# Overview

You are a senior TypeScript engineer.

Build the module src/core/calculations/average.ts.

Purpose:
- Calculate student averages for an exam.

Business rules:
- Each student has multiple scores (notes).
- Each score is linked to an exam subject (épreuve).
- A subject may have a coefficient.
- If at least one coefficient exists, use weighted average.
- If no coefficient exists, use simple average.
- Missing notes are ignored.
- Final average must be rounded to 2 decimals.

Input types:
- StudentScore { subjectId: string; score: number; coefficient?: number }

Output:
- number (average)

Requirements:
- Pure function
- No database access
- No UI logic
- Export function calculateStudentAverage()

Add full TypeScript types and comments.
